      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "URANA QUASAR (1) resumed in a Grade 5 at this track and ran into the frame when second over 515m (30.10). Will be much improved. The form from his last run stacks up well. Makes plenty of appeal. JUNEAU QUADRANT (2) has been in the money at his last two runs, most recently when third (20.12) in a Restricted WIN over 340m at Hobart. Rates a winning chance on best. JUNEAU PETE (3) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 5.5 lengths at Hobart in a handy 25.86 beating Crackerjack Oak. Winner at his latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Expected to measure up again. SEATON (7) must be respected at his pet distance.",
